-- Bill Beaumont Named Chairman of England’s Rugby Football Union
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-07-08T14:44:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-08/bill-beaumont-named-chairman-of-england-s-rugby-football-union.html
Bill Beaumont was today appointed
chairman of  England ’s Rugby Football Union after the
organization’s annual general meeting.  The 60-year-old former England and British & Irish Lions
captain succeeds Paul Murphy, who becomes RFU president in
succession to Willie Wildash.  “I’m very honored to be appointed chairman of the RFU,”
Beaumont said in a  statement . “I was fortunate enough to captain
my country, and everything since then has been about putting
something back into a game that is important to so many
people.’’  England will host rugby’s World Cup in 2015.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  